34JsepTransportDescription::JsepTransportDescription() {}
35
36JsepTransportDescription::JsepTransportDescription(
37 bool rtcp_mux_enabled,
38 const std::vector<CryptoParams>& cryptos,
39 const std::vector<int>& encrypted_header_extension_ids,
40 int rtp_abs_sendtime_extn_id,
41 const TransportDescription& transport_desc)
42 : rtcp_mux_enabled(rtcp_mux_enabled),
43 cryptos(cryptos),
44 encrypted_header_extension_ids(encrypted_header_extension_ids),
45 rtp_abs_sendtime_extn_id(rtp_abs_sendtime_extn_id),
46 transport_desc(transport_desc) {}
47
48JsepTransportDescription::JsepTransportDescription(
49 const JsepTransportDescription& from)
50 : rtcp_mux_enabled(from.rtcp_mux_enabled),
51 cryptos(from.cryptos),
52 encrypted_header_extension_ids(from.encrypted_header_extension_ids),
53 rtp_abs_sendtime_extn_id(from.rtp_abs_sendtime_extn_id),
54 transport_desc(from.transport_desc) {}
55
56JsepTransportDescription::~JsepTransportDescription() = default;
57
58JsepTransportDescription& JsepTransportDescription::operator=(
59 const JsepTransportDescription& from) {
60 if (this == &from) {
61 return *this;
62 }
63 rtcp_mux_enabled = from.rtcp_mux_enabled;
64 cryptos = from.cryptos;
65 encrypted_header_extension_ids = from.encrypted_header_extension_ids;
66 rtp_abs_sendtime_extn_id = from.rtp_abs_sendtime_extn_id;
67 transport_desc = from.transport_desc;
68
69 return *this;
70}

72JsepTransport::JsepTransport(
73 const std::string& mid,
74 const rtc::scoped_refptr<rtc::RTCCertificate>& local_certificate,
75 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::IceTransportInterface> ice_transport,
76 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::IceTransportInterface> rtcp_ice_transport,
77 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::RtpTransport> unencrypted_rtp_transport,
78 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::SrtpTransport> sdes_transport,
79 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::DtlsSrtpTransport> dtls_srtp_transport,
80 std::unique_ptr<DtlsTransportInternal> rtp_dtls_transport,
81 std::unique_ptr<DtlsTransportInternal> rtcp_dtls_transport,
82 std::unique_ptr<SctpTransportInternal> sctp_transport)
83 : network_thread_(rtc::Thread::Current()),
84 mid_(mid),
85 local_certificate_(local_certificate),
86 ice_transport_(std::move(ice_transport)),
87 rtcp_ice_transport_(std::move(rtcp_ice_transport)),
88 unencrypted_rtp_transport_(std::move(unencrypted_rtp_transport)),
89 sdes_transport_(std::move(sdes_transport)),
90 dtls_srtp_transport_(std::move(dtls_srtp_transport)),
91 rtp_dtls_transport_(rtp_dtls_transport
92 ? rtc::make_ref_counted<webrtc::DtlsTransport>(
93 std::move(rtp_dtls_transport))
94 : nullptr),
95 rtcp_dtls_transport_(rtcp_dtls_transport
96 ? rtc::make_ref_counted<webrtc::DtlsTransport>(
97 std::move(rtcp_dtls_transport))
98 : nullptr),
99 sctp_data_channel_transport_(
100 sctp_transport ? std::make_unique<webrtc::SctpDataChannelTransport>(
101 sctp_transport.get())
102 : nullptr),
103 sctp_transport_(sctp_transport
104 ? rtc::make_ref_counted<webrtc::SctpTransport>(
105 std::move(sctp_transport))
106 : nullptr) {
107 RTC_DCHECK(ice_transport_);
108 RTC_DCHECK(rtp_dtls_transport_);
109 // |rtcp_ice_transport_| must be present iff |rtcp_dtls_transport_| is
110 // present.
111 RTC_DCHECK_EQ((rtcp_ice_transport_ != nullptr),
112 (rtcp_dtls_transport_ != nullptr));
113 // Verify the "only one out of these three can be set" invariant.
114 if (unencrypted_rtp_transport_) {
115 RTC_DCHECK(!sdes_transport);
116 RTC_DCHECK(!dtls_srtp_transport);
117 } else if (sdes_transport_) {
118 RTC_DCHECK(!unencrypted_rtp_transport);
119 RTC_DCHECK(!dtls_srtp_transport);
120 } else {
121 RTC_DCHECK(dtls_srtp_transport_);
122 RTC_DCHECK(!unencrypted_rtp_transport);
123 RTC_DCHECK(!sdes_transport);
124 }
125
126 if (sctp_transport_) {
127 sctp_transport_->SetDtlsTransport(rtp_dtls_transport_);
128 }
129}
130
131JsepTransport::~JsepTransport() {
132 if (sctp_transport_) {
133 sctp_transport_->Clear();
134 }
135
136 // Clear all DtlsTransports. There may be pointers to these from
137 // other places, so we can't assume they'll be deleted by the destructor.
138 rtp_dtls_transport_->Clear();
139 if (rtcp_dtls_transport_) {
140 rtcp_dtls_transport_->Clear();
141 }
142
143 // ICE will be the last transport to be deleted.
144}

146webrtc::RTCError JsepTransport::SetLocalJsepTransportDescription(
147 const JsepTransportDescription& jsep_description,
148 SdpType type) {
149 webrtc::RTCError error;
150
151 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
152
153 IceParameters ice_parameters =
154 jsep_description.transport_desc.GetIceParameters();
155 webrtc::RTCError ice_parameters_result = ice_parameters.Validate();
156 if (!ice_parameters_result.ok()) {
157 rtc::StringBuilder sb;
158 sb << "Invalid ICE parameters: " << ice_parameters_result.message();
159 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
160 sb.Release());
161 }
162
163 if (!SetRtcpMux(jsep_description.rtcp_mux_enabled, type,
164 ContentSource::CS_LOCAL)) {
165 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
166 "Failed to setup RTCP mux.");
167 }
168
169 // If doing SDES, setup the SDES crypto parameters.
170 if (sdes_transport_) {
171 RTC_DCHECK(!unencrypted_rtp_transport_);
172 RTC_DCHECK(!dtls_srtp_transport_);
173 if (!SetSdes(jsep_description.cryptos,
174 jsep_description.encrypted_header_extension_ids, type,
175 ContentSource::CS_LOCAL)) {
176 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
177 "Failed to setup SDES crypto parameters.");
178 }
179 } else if (dtls_srtp_transport_) {
180 RTC_DCHECK(!unencrypted_rtp_transport_);
181 RTC_DCHECK(!sdes_transport_);
182 dtls_srtp_transport_->UpdateRecvEncryptedHeaderExtensionIds(
183 jsep_description.encrypted_header_extension_ids);
184 }
185 bool ice_restarting =
186 local_description_ != nullptr &&
187 IceCredentialsChanged(local_description_->transport_desc.ice_ufrag,
188 local_description_->transport_desc.ice_pwd,
189 ice_parameters.ufrag, ice_parameters.pwd);
190 local_description_.reset(new JsepTransportDescription(jsep_description));
191
192 rtc::SSLFingerprint* local_fp =
193 local_description_->transport_desc.identity_fingerprint.get();
194
195 if (!local_fp) {
196 local_certificate_ = nullptr;
197 } else {
198 error = VerifyCertificateFingerprint(local_certificate_, local_fp);
199 if (!error.ok()) {
200 local_description_.reset();
201 return error;
202 }
203 }
204 RTC_DCHECK(rtp_dtls_transport_->internal());
205 rtp_dtls_transport_->internal()->ice_transport()->SetIceParameters(
206 ice_parameters);
207
208 {
209 if (rtcp_dtls_transport_) {
210 RTC_DCHECK(rtcp_dtls_transport_->internal());
211 rtcp_dtls_transport_->internal()->ice_transport()->SetIceParameters(
212 ice_parameters);
213 }
214 }
215 // If PRANSWER/ANSWER is set, we should decide transport protocol type.
216 if (type == SdpType::kPrAnswer || type == SdpType::kAnswer) {
217 error = NegotiateAndSetDtlsParameters(type);
218 }
219 if (!error.ok()) {
220 local_description_.reset();
221 return error;
222 }
223
224 if (needs_ice_restart_ && ice_restarting) {
225 needs_ice_restart_ = false;
226 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "needs-ice-restart flag cleared for transport "
227 << mid();
228 }
229
230 return webrtc::RTCError::OK();
231}
232
233webrtc::RTCError JsepTransport::SetRemoteJsepTransportDescription(
234 const JsepTransportDescription& jsep_description,
235 webrtc::SdpType type) {
236 webrtc::RTCError error;
237
238 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
239
240 IceParameters ice_parameters =
241 jsep_description.transport_desc.GetIceParameters();
242 webrtc::RTCError ice_parameters_result = ice_parameters.Validate();
243 if (!ice_parameters_result.ok()) {
244 remote_description_.reset();
245 rtc::StringBuilder sb;
246 sb << "Invalid ICE parameters: " << ice_parameters_result.message();
247 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
248 sb.Release());
249 }
250
251 if (!SetRtcpMux(jsep_description.rtcp_mux_enabled, type,
252 ContentSource::CS_REMOTE)) {
253 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
254 "Failed to setup RTCP mux.");
255 }
256
257 // If doing SDES, setup the SDES crypto parameters.
258 if (sdes_transport_) {
259 RTC_DCHECK(!unencrypted_rtp_transport_);
260 RTC_DCHECK(!dtls_srtp_transport_);
261 if (!SetSdes(jsep_description.cryptos,
262 jsep_description.encrypted_header_extension_ids, type,
263 ContentSource::CS_REMOTE)) {
264 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
265 "Failed to setup SDES crypto parameters.");
266 }
267 sdes_transport_->CacheRtpAbsSendTimeHeaderExtension(
268 jsep_description.rtp_abs_sendtime_extn_id);
269 } else if (dtls_srtp_transport_) {
270 RTC_DCHECK(!unencrypted_rtp_transport_);
271 RTC_DCHECK(!sdes_transport_);
272 dtls_srtp_transport_->UpdateSendEncryptedHeaderExtensionIds(
273 jsep_description.encrypted_header_extension_ids);
274 dtls_srtp_transport_->CacheRtpAbsSendTimeHeaderExtension(
275 jsep_description.rtp_abs_sendtime_extn_id);
276 }
277
278 remote_description_.reset(new JsepTransportDescription(jsep_description));
279 RTC_DCHECK(rtp_dtls_transport());
280 SetRemoteIceParameters(ice_parameters, rtp_dtls_transport()->ice_transport());
281
282 if (rtcp_dtls_transport()) {
283 SetRemoteIceParameters(ice_parameters,
284 rtcp_dtls_transport()->ice_transport());
285 }
286
287 // If PRANSWER/ANSWER is set, we should decide transport protocol type.
288 if (type == SdpType::kPrAnswer || type == SdpType::kAnswer) {
289 error = NegotiateAndSetDtlsParameters(SdpType::kOffer);
290 }
291 if (!error.ok()) {
292 remote_description_.reset();
293 return error;
294 }
295 return webrtc::RTCError::OK();
296}
297
298webrtc::RTCError JsepTransport::AddRemoteCandidates(
299 const Candidates& candidates) {
300 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
301 if (!local_description_ || !remote_description_) {
302 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_STATE,
303 mid() +
304 " is not ready to use the remote candidate "
305 "because the local or remote description is "
306 "not set.");
307 }
308
309 for (const cricket::Candidate& candidate : candidates) {
310 auto transport =
311 candidate.component() == cricket::ICE_CANDIDATE_COMPONENT_RTP
312 ? rtp_dtls_transport_
313 : rtcp_dtls_transport_;
314 if (!transport) {
315 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
316 "Candidate has an unknown component: " +
317 candidate.ToSensitiveString() + " for mid " +
318 mid());
319 }
320 RTC_DCHECK(transport->internal() && transport->internal()->ice_transport());
321 transport->internal()->ice_transport()->AddRemoteCandidate(candidate);
322 }
323 return webrtc::RTCError::OK();
324}

326void JsepTransport::SetNeedsIceRestartFlag() {
327 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
328 if (!needs_ice_restart_) {
329 needs_ice_restart_ = true;
330 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "needs-ice-restart flag set for transport " << mid();
331 }

334absl::optional<rtc::SSLRole> JsepTransport::GetDtlsRole() const {
335 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
336 RTC_DCHECK(rtp_dtls_transport_);
337 RTC_DCHECK(rtp_dtls_transport_->internal());
338 rtc::SSLRole dtls_role;
339 if (!rtp_dtls_transport_->internal()->GetDtlsRole(&dtls_role)) {
340 return absl::optional<rtc::SSLRole>();
341 }
342
343 return absl::optional<rtc::SSLRole>(dtls_role);
344}

346bool JsepTransport::GetStats(TransportStats* stats) {
347 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
348 stats->transport_name = mid();
349 stats->channel_stats.clear();
350 RTC_DCHECK(rtp_dtls_transport_->internal());
351 bool ret = GetTransportStats(rtp_dtls_transport_->internal(),
352 ICE_CANDIDATE_COMPONENT_RTP, stats);
353
354 if (rtcp_dtls_transport_) {
355 RTC_DCHECK(rtcp_dtls_transport_->internal());
356 ret &= GetTransportStats(rtcp_dtls_transport_->internal(),
357 ICE_CANDIDATE_COMPONENT_RTCP, stats);
358 }
359 return ret;
360}

362webrtc::RTCError JsepTransport::VerifyCertificateFingerprint(
363 const rtc::RTCCertificate* certificate,
364 const rtc::SSLFingerprint* fingerprint) const {
365 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
366 if (!fingerprint) {
367 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
368 "No fingerprint");
369 }
370 if (!certificate) {
371 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
372 "Fingerprint provided but no identity available.");
373 }
374 std::unique_ptr<rtc::SSLFingerprint> fp_tmp =
375 rtc::SSLFingerprint::CreateUnique(fingerprint->algorithm,
376 *certificate->identity());
377 RTC_DCHECK(fp_tmp.get() != NULL);
378 if (*fp_tmp == *fingerprint) {
379 return webrtc::RTCError::OK();
380 }
381 char ss_buf[1024];
382 rtc::SimpleStringBuilder desc(ss_buf);
383 desc << "Local fingerprint does not match identity. Expected: ";
384 desc << fp_tmp->ToString();
385 desc << " Got: " << fingerprint->ToString();
386 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
387 std::string(desc.str()));
388}

409
410webrtc::RTCError JsepTransport::SetNegotiatedDtlsParameters(
411 DtlsTransportInternal* dtls_transport,
412 absl::optional<rtc::SSLRole> dtls_role,
413 rtc::SSLFingerprint* remote_fingerprint) {
414 RTC_DCHECK(dtls_transport);
415 // Set SSL role. Role must be set before fingerprint is applied, which
416 // initiates DTLS setup.
417 if (dtls_role && !dtls_transport->SetDtlsRole(*dtls_role)) {
418 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
419 "Failed to set SSL role for the transport.");
420 }
421 // Apply remote fingerprint.
422 if (!remote_fingerprint ||
423 !dtls_transport->SetRemoteFingerprint(
424 remote_fingerprint->algorithm, remote_fingerprint->digest.cdata(),
425 remote_fingerprint->digest.size())) {
426 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
427 "Failed to apply remote fingerprint.");
428 }
429 return webrtc::RTCError::OK();
430}
431
432bool JsepTransport::SetRtcpMux(bool enable,
433 webrtc::SdpType type,
434 ContentSource source) {
435 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
436 bool ret = false;
437 switch (type) {
438 case SdpType::kOffer:
439 ret = rtcp_mux_negotiator_.SetOffer(enable, source);
440 break;
441 case SdpType::kPrAnswer:
442 // This may activate RTCP muxing, but we don't yet destroy the transport
443 // because the final answer may deactivate it.
444 ret = rtcp_mux_negotiator_.SetProvisionalAnswer(enable, source);
445 break;
446 case SdpType::kAnswer:
447 ret = rtcp_mux_negotiator_.SetAnswer(enable, source);
448 if (ret && rtcp_mux_negotiator_.IsActive()) {
449 ActivateRtcpMux();
450 }
451 break;
452 default:
453 RTC_NOTREACHED();
454 }
455
456 if (!ret) {
457 return false;
458 }
459
460 auto transport = rtp_transport();
461 transport->SetRtcpMuxEnabled(rtcp_mux_negotiator_.IsActive());
462 return ret;
463}
464
465void JsepTransport::ActivateRtcpMux() {
466 if (unencrypted_rtp_transport_) {
467 RTC_DCHECK(!sdes_transport_);
468 RTC_DCHECK(!dtls_srtp_transport_);
469 unencrypted_rtp_transport_->SetRtcpPacketTransport(nullptr);
470 } else if (sdes_transport_) {
471 RTC_DCHECK(!unencrypted_rtp_transport_);
472 RTC_DCHECK(!dtls_srtp_transport_);
473 sdes_transport_->SetRtcpPacketTransport(nullptr);
474 } else if (dtls_srtp_transport_) {
475 RTC_DCHECK(dtls_srtp_transport_);
476 RTC_DCHECK(!unencrypted_rtp_transport_);
477 RTC_DCHECK(!sdes_transport_);
478 dtls_srtp_transport_->SetDtlsTransports(rtp_dtls_transport(),
479 /*rtcp_dtls_transport=*/nullptr);
480 }
481 rtcp_dtls_transport_ = nullptr; // Destroy this reference.
482 // Notify the JsepTransportController to update the aggregate states.
483 SignalRtcpMuxActive();
484}
485
486bool JsepTransport::SetSdes(const std::vector<CryptoParams>& cryptos,
487 const std::vector<int>& encrypted_extension_ids,
488 webrtc::SdpType type,
489 ContentSource source) {
490 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
491 bool ret = false;
492 ret = sdes_negotiator_.Process(cryptos, type, source);
493 if (!ret) {
494 return ret;
495 }
496
497 if (source == ContentSource::CS_LOCAL) {
498 recv_extension_ids_ = encrypted_extension_ids;
499 } else {
500 send_extension_ids_ = encrypted_extension_ids;
501 }
502
503 // If setting an SDES answer succeeded, apply the negotiated parameters
504 // to the SRTP transport.
505 if ((type == SdpType::kPrAnswer || type == SdpType::kAnswer) && ret) {
506 if (sdes_negotiator_.send_cipher_suite() &&
507 sdes_negotiator_.recv_cipher_suite()) {
508 RTC_DCHECK(send_extension_ids_);
509 RTC_DCHECK(recv_extension_ids_);
510 ret = sdes_transport_->SetRtpParams(
511 *(sdes_negotiator_.send_cipher_suite()),
512 sdes_negotiator_.send_key().data(),
513 static_cast<int>(sdes_negotiator_.send_key().size()),
514 *(send_extension_ids_), *(sdes_negotiator_.recv_cipher_suite()),
515 sdes_negotiator_.recv_key().data(),
516 static_cast<int>(sdes_negotiator_.recv_key().size()),
517 *(recv_extension_ids_));
518 } else {
519 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "No crypto keys are provided for SDES.";
520 if (type == SdpType::kAnswer) {
521 // Explicitly reset the |sdes_transport_| if no crypto param is
522 // provided in the answer. No need to call |ResetParams()| for
523 // |sdes_negotiator_| because it resets the params inside |SetAnswer|.
524 sdes_transport_->ResetParams();
525 }
526 }
527 }
528 return ret;
529}
530
531webrtc::RTCError JsepTransport::NegotiateAndSetDtlsParameters(
532 SdpType local_description_type) {
533 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
534 if (!local_description_ || !remote_description_) {
535 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_STATE,
536 "Applying an answer transport description "
537 "without applying any offer.");
538 }
539 std::unique_ptr<rtc::SSLFingerprint> remote_fingerprint;
540 absl::optional<rtc::SSLRole> negotiated_dtls_role;
541
542 rtc::SSLFingerprint* local_fp =
543 local_description_->transport_desc.identity_fingerprint.get();
544 rtc::SSLFingerprint* remote_fp =
545 remote_description_->transport_desc.identity_fingerprint.get();
546 if (remote_fp && local_fp) {
547 remote_fingerprint = std::make_unique<rtc::SSLFingerprint>(*remote_fp);
548 webrtc::RTCError error =
549 NegotiateDtlsRole(local_description_type,
550 local_description_->transport_desc.connection_role,
551 remote_description_->transport_desc.connection_role,
552 &negotiated_dtls_role);
553 if (!error.ok()) {
554 return error;
555 }
556 } else if (local_fp && (local_description_type == SdpType::kAnswer)) {
557 return webrtc::RTCError(
558 webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
559 "Local fingerprint supplied when caller didn't offer DTLS.");
560 } else {
561 // We are not doing DTLS
562 remote_fingerprint = std::make_unique<rtc::SSLFingerprint>(
563 "", rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t>());
564 }
565 // Now that we have negotiated everything, push it downward.
566 // Note that we cache the result so that if we have race conditions
567 // between future SetRemote/SetLocal invocations and new transport
568 // creation, we have the negotiation state saved until a new
569 // negotiation happens.
570 RTC_DCHECK(rtp_dtls_transport());
571 webrtc::RTCError error = SetNegotiatedDtlsParameters(
572 rtp_dtls_transport(), negotiated_dtls_role, remote_fingerprint.get());
573 if (!error.ok()) {
574 return error;
575 }
576
577 if (rtcp_dtls_transport()) {
578 error = SetNegotiatedDtlsParameters(
579 rtcp_dtls_transport(), negotiated_dtls_role, remote_fingerprint.get());
580 }
581 return error;
582}
583
584webrtc::RTCError JsepTransport::NegotiateDtlsRole(
585 SdpType local_description_type,
586 ConnectionRole local_connection_role,
587 ConnectionRole remote_connection_role,
588 absl::optional<rtc::SSLRole>* negotiated_dtls_role) {
589 // From RFC 4145, section-4.1, The following are the values that the
590 // 'setup' attribute can take in an offer/answer exchange:
591 // Offer Answer
592 // ________________
593 // active passive / holdconn
594 // passive active / holdconn
595 // actpass active / passive / holdconn
596 // holdconn holdconn
597 //
598 // Set the role that is most conformant with RFC 5763, Section 5, bullet 1
599 // The endpoint MUST use the setup attribute defined in [RFC4145].
600 // The endpoint that is the offerer MUST use the setup attribute
601 // value of setup:actpass and be prepared to receive a client_hello
602 // before it receives the answer. The answerer MUST use either a
603 // setup attribute value of setup:active or setup:passive. Note that
604 // if the answerer uses setup:passive, then the DTLS handshake will
605 // not begin until the answerer is received, which adds additional
606 // latency. setup:active allows the answer and the DTLS handshake to
607 // occur in parallel. Thus, setup:active is RECOMMENDED. Whichever
608 // party is active MUST initiate a DTLS handshake by sending a
609 // ClientHello over each flow (host/port quartet).
610 // IOW - actpass and passive modes should be treated as server and
611 // active as client.
612 bool is_remote_server = false;
613 if (local_description_type == SdpType::kOffer) {
614 if (local_connection_role != CONNECTIONROLE_ACTPASS) {
615 return webrtc::RTCError(
616 webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
617 "Offerer must use actpass value for setup attribute.");
618 }
619
620 if (remote_connection_role == CONNECTIONROLE_ACTIVE ||
621 remote_connection_role == CONNECTIONROLE_PASSIVE ||
622 remote_connection_role == CONNECTIONROLE_NONE) {
623 is_remote_server = (remote_connection_role == CONNECTIONROLE_PASSIVE);
624 } else {
625 return webrtc::RTCError(
626 webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
627 "Answerer must use either active or passive value "
628 "for setup attribute.");
629 }
630 // If remote is NONE or ACTIVE it will act as client.
631 } else {
632 if (remote_connection_role != CONNECTIONROLE_ACTPASS &&
633 remote_connection_role != CONNECTIONROLE_NONE) {
634 // Accept a remote role attribute that's not "actpass", but matches the
635 // current negotiated role. This is allowed by dtls-sdp, though our
636 // implementation will never generate such an offer as it's not
637 // recommended.
638 //
639 // See https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/draft-ietf-mmusic-dtls-sdp,
640 // section 5.5.
641 auto current_dtls_role = GetDtlsRole();
642 if (!current_dtls_role ||
643 (*current_dtls_role == rtc::SSL_CLIENT &&
644 remote_connection_role == CONNECTIONROLE_ACTIVE) ||
645 (*current_dtls_role == rtc::SSL_SERVER &&
646 remote_connection_role == CONNECTIONROLE_PASSIVE)) {
647 return webrtc::RTCError(
648 webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
649 "Offerer must use actpass value or current negotiated role for "
650 "setup attribute.");
651 }
652 }
653
654 if (local_connection_role == CONNECTIONROLE_ACTIVE ||
655 local_connection_role == CONNECTIONROLE_PASSIVE) {
656 is_remote_server = (local_connection_role == CONNECTIONROLE_ACTIVE);
657 } else {
658 return webrtc::RTCError(
659 webrtc::RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
660 "Answerer must use either active or passive value "
661 "for setup attribute.");
662 }
663
664 // If local is passive, local will act as server.
665 }
666
667 *negotiated_dtls_role =
668 (is_remote_server ? rtc::SSL_CLIENT : rtc::SSL_SERVER);
669 return webrtc::RTCError::OK();
670}
671
672bool JsepTransport::GetTransportStats(DtlsTransportInternal* dtls_transport,
673 int component,
674 TransportStats* stats) {
675 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
676 RTC_DCHECK(dtls_transport);
677 TransportChannelStats substats;
678 substats.component = component;
679 dtls_transport->GetSslVersionBytes(&substats.ssl_version_bytes);
680 dtls_transport->GetSrtpCryptoSuite(&substats.srtp_crypto_suite);
681 dtls_transport->GetSslCipherSuite(&substats.ssl_cipher_suite);
682 substats.dtls_state = dtls_transport->dtls_state();
683 if (!dtls_transport->ice_transport()->GetStats(
684 &substats.ice_transport_stats)) {
685 return false;
686 }
687 stats->channel_stats.push_back(substats);
688 return true;
689}
